The paper discusses debugging transactions in OLAP applications, tracing errors in production systems, and auditing database operations. These topics are closely related to database systems (cs.DB) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also presents a declarative replay technique (reenactment) for replaying transactions over the state of the DB, which involves programming languages and compilers (cs.PL). Additionally, the paper mentions the importance of concurrency control and the potential impact of concurrently running transactions, which are topics in cryptography and security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG).
